      <description>A detail of a mosaic. located in the Corridor of the Great Hunt, at Villa Romana
         del Casale at Piazza Armerina. The overall mosaic depicts a large-scale hunt for wild
         animals, which are to be sold to be used for entertainment. Within the detail several
         hunters with shields are shown, several on horseback, with one being attacked by a wounded
         lion (top-left). Two more hunters are shown driving an ox-drawn cart (bottom-right),
         presumably filled with captured animals. A lion and leopard are also depicted (top-right)
         hunting gazelle. </description>
